headline: Is Dominion Energy (D) Pricing In Too Much Stability After Its Recent 14.5% Gain?
summary: If you have ever wondered whether Dominion Energy is fairly priced or if there is still value on the table, this breakdown is designed to give you a clear, grounded view. Over the past year, the stock has delivered a 14.5% return, with 7 day, 30 day and year to date returns of 3.6%, 2.9% and 3.2% respectively. This has drawn fresh attention to what investors are paying for each dollar of the business. Recent coverage has focused on how a regulated utility like Dominion Energy fits into...

headline: Dominion Energy Charitable Foundation Spring Grant Cycle Now Open
summary: RICHMOND, Va., January 20, 2026--Nonprofit organizations within Dominion Energy's service areas are invited to apply for grants from the Dominion Energy Charitable Foundation.
